hpo_terms.prompt:
Extract HPO phenotype terms from the following clinical note for a pancreatic cancer patient. For each finding, provide the best-matching HPO ID and term name. Focus on: abdominal pain, jaundice, weight loss, diabetes, pancreatitis, nausea, vomiting, back pain, ascites, fatigue, thrombosis, depression.

Clinical Note: {note}

Return a JSON array of objects with keys: hpo_id, hpo_term, confidence (0-1), evidence_span.

tumor_characteristics.prompt:
Extract tumor characteristics from the clinical note for a pancreatic cancer patient. Identify: tumor location (head/body/tail of pancreas), size in cm, TNM stage if mentioned, histologic type (e.g. ductal adenocarcinoma, IPMN, NET), and grade.

Clinical Note: {note}

Return a JSON object with keys: tumor_location, tumor_size_cm, tnm_stage, histology, grade, confidence (0-1).

biomarker_status.prompt:
Extract biomarker and molecular testing results from the clinical note. Look for: KRAS mutation status, MSI status (MSI-H/MSS), TMB value, HER2 status, NTRK fusion status, dMMR status, BRCA1/2 status, TP53 status, SMAD4 status, CDKN2A status.

Clinical Note: {note}

Return a JSON array of objects with keys: biomarker, result, method (IHC/NGS/PCR), confidence (0-1).

treatment_history.prompt:
Extract treatment history from the clinical note for a pancreatic cancer patient. Identify: surgical procedures (Whipple, distal pancreatectomy, etc.), chemotherapy regimens (FOLFIRINOX, gemcitabine/nab-paclitaxel, etc.), radiation therapy, targeted therapy, clinical trial participation.

Clinical Note: {note}

Return a JSON array of objects with keys: treatment, type (surgery/chemo/radiation/targeted), date_or_status, confidence (0-1).
